#: index.docbook:505
msgid "Installation"
msgstr "Installation"

#: index.docbook:508
msgid "How to obtain &ktalkd;"
msgstr "Wie man &ktalkd; erhält"

#: index.docbook:510
msgid ""
"&ktalkd; is now a core application of the &kde; project <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org\">http://www.kde.org</ulink>, part of the "
"kdenetwork package."
msgstr ""
"&ktalkd; ist nun im Paket kdenetwork von &kde; unter <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org\">http://www.kde.org</ulink> enthalten."

#: index.docbook:516
msgid ""
"You can always download the latest &ktalkd; from the main &FTP; site of the "
"&kde; project, <ulink "
"url=\"ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde\">ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde</ulink>"
" and from its mirrors. It's usually found in <ulink "
"url=\"ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/stable/latest/apps/network\">"
"ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/stable/latest/apps/network</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Aber Sie können die neueste Version von &ktalkd; immer von der "
"Haupt-&FTP;-Seite des &kde;-Projekts <ulink "
"url=\"ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde\">ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde</ulink> und "
"seinen Spiegelservern herunter laden. Sie finden es normalerweise in <ulink "
"url=\"ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/stable/latest/apps/network\">"
"ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/stable/latest/apps/network</ulink>."

#: index.docbook:526
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr "Anforderungen"

#: index.docbook:528
msgid ""
"In order to successfully compile &ktalkd;, you need the latest versions of "
"the &kde; libraries as well as the &Qt; C++ library. All required libraries "
"as well as ktalkd itself can be found on <ulink "
"url=\"ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/\">ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Um &ktalkd; erfolgreich zu kompilieren, brauchen Sie die neueste Version der "
"&kde; Bibliotheken und die &Qt; C++ Bibliothek. Alle benötigten "
"Bibliotheken sowie auch &ktalkd; selbst finden Sie auf <ulink "
"url=\"ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/\">ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/</ulink>."

#: index.docbook:537
msgid "Compilation and Installation"
msgstr "Übersetzung und Installation"

#: index.docbook:539
msgid ""
"In order to compile and install &ktalkd; on your system, type the following "
"in the base directory of the &ktalkd; distribution:"
msgstr ""
"Um &ktalkd; auf Ihrem System zu kompilieren und zu installieren, geben Sie "
"bitte folgendes im Basisverzeichnis der &ktalkd; Distribution ein:"

#: index.docbook:544
msgid ""
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>./configure</command></userinput>\n"
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>make</command></userinput> \n"
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>make</command> "
"<option>install</option></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>./configure</command></userinput>\n"
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>make</command></userinput> \n"
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>make</command> "
"<option>install</option></userinput>"

#: index.docbook:550
msgid ""
"As &ktalkd; is a daemon, <userinput><command>make</command> "
"<option>install</option></userinput> will require <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> privileges."
msgstr ""
"Da &ktalkd; ein Dämon ist, erfordert der Befehl "
"<userinput><command>make</command> <option>install</option></userinput> "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>-Berechtigungen."

#: index.docbook:556
msgid ""
"Don't forget to update <filename>/etc/inetd.conf</filename>"
". For example, on a &Linux; system, if &kde; is in <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/opt/kde</filename>, change the lines concerning "
"<command>talk</command> and <command>ntalk</command> to:"
msgstr ""
"Wichtig ist, die Datei <filename>/etc/inetd.conf</filename> anzupassen. Zum "
"Beispiel müssen für ein &Linux;-System mit &kde; in <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/opt/kde</filename> die Zeilen, die "
"<command>talk</command> und <command>ntalk</command> betreffen, "
"folgendermaßen geändert werden:"

#: index.docbook:563
msgid ""
"talk   dgram   udp     wait    root    /usr/sbin/tcpd  /opt/kde/bin/kotalkd\n"
"ntalk  dgram   udp     wait    root    /usr/sbin/tcpd  /opt/kde/bin/ktalkd"
msgstr ""
"talk   dgram   udp     wait    root    /usr/sbin/tcpd  /opt/kde/bin/kotalkd\n"
"ntalk  dgram   udp     wait    root    /usr/sbin/tcpd  /opt/kde/bin/ktalkd"

#: index.docbook:568
msgid ""
"A script is provided, to make the necessary change automatically. Update "
"your <filename>inetd.conf</filename> file just by running"
msgstr ""
"Es gibt ein Skript, das die Änderungen automatisch vornimmt. Damit kann man "
"<filename>inetd.conf</filename> durch folgenden Befehl anpassen:"

#: index.docbook:573
msgid ""
"<prompt>%</prompt> "
"<userinput><command>./post-install.sh</command></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>%</prompt> "
"<userinput><command>./post-install.sh</command></userinput>"

#: index.docbook:577
msgid ""
"Anyway, you'll have to <emphasis>restart inetd</emphasis> after this. On "
"most &Linux; systems, do:"
msgstr ""
"In jedem Fall muss inetd danach <emphasis>neugestartet</emphasis> werden. "
"Dazu reicht auf den meisten &Linux;-Systemen der Befehl:"

#: index.docbook:581
msgid ""
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>killall</command> <option>-HUP "
"inetd</option></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<prompt>%</prompt> <userinput><command>killall</command> <option>-HUP "
"inetd</option></userinput>"

#: index.docbook:585
msgid ""
"On newer systems, using <command>xinetd</command>, there is no more "
"<filename>/etc/inetd.conf</filename>, and you should edit or create "
"<filename>/etc/xinetd.d/talk</filename> instead, with those lines:"
msgstr ""
"Auf neueren Systemen, die <command>xinetd</command>"
" verwenden, gibt es keine Datei <filename>inetd.conf</filename> mehr. "
"Stattdessen muss die Datei <filename>/etc/xinetd.d/talk</filename> mit "
"folgenden Zeilen geändert oder erzeugt werden:"

#: index.docbook:591
msgid ""
"service talk\n"
"{\n"
"\tsocket_type = dgram\n"
"\twait = yes\n"
"\tuser = root\n"
"\tserver = /usr/bin/kotalkd\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"service ntalk\n"
"{\n"
"\tsocket_type = dgram\n"
"\twait = yes\n"
"\tuser = root\n"
"\tserver = /usr/bin/ktalkd\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"service talk\n"
"{\n"
"\tsocket_type = dgram\n"
"\twait = yes\n"
"\tuser = root\n"
"\tserver = /usr/bin/kotalkd\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"service ntalk\n"
"{\n"
"\tsocket_type = dgram\n"
"\twait = yes\n"
"\tuser = root\n"
"\tserver = /usr/bin/ktalkd\n"
"}"

#: index.docbook:609
msgid "then restart <command>xinetd</command>."
msgstr "Dann muss <command>xinetd</command> neu gestartet werden."

